# Nuxt 3 + Vue 3 — Project Rules

## Code style

- Functional and declarative patterns — avoid classes
- Composition API with `<script setup>` only — never Options API
- Descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `isVisible`, `hasContent`
- Named exports for composables and utilities — default exports only for Vue components and Nuxt config

## Naming conventions

- Components: PascalCase (`components/WorkCard.vue`)
- Composables: camelCase with `use` prefix (`composables/usePrefersReducedMotion.ts`)
- Pages: lowercase with dashes (`pages/about.vue`, `pages/work/[slug].vue`)

## Auto-imports

Nuxt auto-imports Vue and Nuxt primitives — never import them manually.

Exception: `motion` from `motion-v` is not auto-imported and must always be imported manually.

## State management

- Local state: `ref` / `reactive`
- SSR-safe shared state: `useState`
- Pinia is not installed — do not reach for it

## SEO

- Every page must define metadata
- Use `useSeoMeta` as the default; `useHead` for canonical URLs, Open Graph, structured data
- Never hardcode `<title>` or `<meta>` tags in templates
- Site title suffix: `— designwithjack`

## Images

Static images in `public/images/`, referenced with absolute paths. Use native `<img>` with `width`, `height`, `alt`, and `loading="lazy"`.

## Performance

- Avoid animating layout properties (height, width, padding, margin) — use transform-based alternatives
- Lazy load heavy components with `defineAsyncComponent`
